## 📊 Database Schema

### developers table
```
id (SERIAL PK) | name | project | contract_status | created_at | updated_at
```

### performances table
```
id (SERIAL PK) | developer_id (FK) | completed_features | bug_count | 
performance_score | created_at | updated_at
```

---

## 🔍 How It Works

### User Input Flow
```
User Input (Form1)
    ↓
Validation
    ↓
DeveloperService.AddDeveloperAsync()
    ↓
DeveloperRepository.AddDeveloperAsync()
    ↓
DatabaseConnection.ExecuteAsync()
    ↓
PostgreSQL (INSERT query)
    ↓
Data saved ✅
    ↓
Refresh DataGridView
```

### Data Retrieval Flow
```
Form1.RefreshDataGridViewAsync()
    ↓
DeveloperService.GetAllDevelopersAsync()
    ↓
DeveloperRepository.GetAllDevelopersAsync()
    ↓
DatabaseConnection.ExecuteReaderAsync()
    ↓
PostgreSQL (SELECT query)
    ↓
Results mapped to objects
    ↓
Display in DataGridView
```

---

## 🛠️ Troubleshooting Quick Reference

| Error | Solution |
|-------|----------|
| "Gagal terhubung ke database" | Check PostgreSQL running, verify connection string |
| "password authentication failed" | Verify password in appsettings.json |
| "relation 'developers' does not exist" | Run schema.sql to create tables |
| "database 'prodev_db' does not exist" | Create database with `CREATE DATABASE prodev_db;` |
| "could not connect to server" | PostgreSQL service not running |

